The paper discusses accelerated coordinate descent methods for optimization problems, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). It also discusses faster algorithms for solving linear systems, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also mentions Kaczmarz methods, which are commonly used in image reconstruction (cs.CV) and overdetermined systems of equations (cs.DS). The paper also discusses convergence guarantees and numerical stability, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT).
